Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
pasteObject(25.10)                                          pasteObject(25.10)

Name
       pasteObject - Pastes copied placement or routing blockages at the spec-
       ified location

Syntax
       pasteObject

       [-help]

       [-loc {<x y>}]

       Pastes copied placement or routing blockages at the specified location.
       Use  the  copyObject command to copy the required object. Use this com-
       mand any time after floorplanning the design. You  can  also  copy  and
       paste  selected  placement  and routing blockages from the GUI by using
       the Copy tool. To access the Copy tool, choose Edit  -  Copy  from  the
       menu bar or press F3 after clicking the Copy widget () on the toolbar.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the pasteObject command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man pasteObject

       -loc {<x y>}
              Specifies the location for pasting the object copy.

              Data_type: point, optional

Example
              * The  following  commands copy and paste the selected placement
                and routing blockages:

                copyObject

                pasteObject -loc 10 20

Related Information
              * copyObject

              * editCopy

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

